ve to `SDK/hik/` or something similar. Let me check.\n\nFrom the output: `C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\SDK`\n\nSo `SDK_LIBS_DIR / \"Sadp.dll\"` = `SDK\\Sadp.dll` which does NOT exist. The DLL is at `SDK\\hik\\Sadp.dll`.\n\nThis is the root cause of the 500 error. The `_find_sadp_dll()` function can't find the DLL because it's looking at `SDK/Sadp.dll` instead of `SDK/hik/Sadp.dll`.\n\nNow the question is: what changed? The DLL has always been at `SDK/hik/Sadp.dll`, and `_find_sadp_dll()` has always been checking `SDK_LIBS_DIR / \"Sadp.dll\"`. So either:\n1. `SDK_LIBS_DIR` used to point to `SDK/hik` but was changed\n2. The DLL used to be at `SDK/Sadp.dll` and was moved to `SDK/hik/`\n\nLet me check config_paths.py to understand what SDK_LIBS_DIR resolves to.\n\nActually wait, let me re-read the error more carefully. The error says:\n```\nFileNotFoundError: Sadp.dll not found. Searched: SDK/hik/Sadp.dll, src/core/Sadp.dll. \n```\n\nBut the code does:\n```python\nsdk_sadp = SDK_LIBS_DIR / \"Sadp.dll\"  # This is SDK/Sadp.dll, NOT SDK/hik/Sadp.dll\n```\n\nHmm, there's a discrepancy. Maybe there's a different version of `_find_sadp_dll` in another file? No, the code I read is the current version.\n\nActually wait, the error message is hardcoded in the raise statement:\n```python\nraise FileNotFoundError(\n    f\"Sadp.dll not found. Searched: \"\n    f\"SDK/hik/Sadp.dll, src/core/Sadp.dll. \"\n    \"Please copy SDK DLLs to SDK/hik/ directory.\"\n)\n```\n\nThis error message was written when the code was searching `SDK/hik/Sadp.dll`. But the actual code now searches `SDK_LIBS_DIR / \"Sadp.dll\"` which is `SDK/Sadp.dll`. So the error message is misleading.\n\nThe actual search path is `SDK_LIBS_DIR / \"Sadp.dll\"` = `C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\SDK\\Sadp.dll` which does NOT exist. The DLL is at `SDK\\hik\\Sadp.dll`.\n\nSo the fix is: change `_find_sadp_dll()` to search `SDK_LIBS_DIR / \"hik\" / \"Sadp.dll\"` (or