{"type":"message","id":"11befbaf","parentId":"c8cf1018","timestamp":"2026-06-29T11:29:12.451Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user asked two things:\n1. Why the device connection interface doesn't show gateway (for the device)\n2. Where is the local machine info (gateway, IP) read from\n\nLet me trace both:\n\n**Local machine info**: \n- Read from `data/reports/localhost.json` (saved once on first run)\n- Collected by `src/advanced/startup.py::collect_localhost_info()`\n- Gateway: `get_default_gateway()` uses `Get-NetRoute -DestinationPrefix 0.0.0.0/0` PowerShell\n- Local IP: `get_local_ip()` from `src/core/net_detector::get_all_nics()`\n\n**Device gateway**: \n- SADP discovery returns gateway from the SADP DLL callback (device's own gateway from `SADP_DEVICE_INFO.szIPv4Gateway`)\n- But the devices API endpoint merges SADP + stored devices, and the stored devices may not have gateway\n- Let me check the devices endpoint to see why it's not showing gateway\n\nThe `/api/v1/devices` returned 0 devices. But SADP discovery shows gateway. Let me look at the renderDevices function which shows `d.gateway || '--'` in the table. The question is why the frontend isn't showing it.\n\nWait, the `/api/v1/devices` returned 0 devices - that seems wrong. Let me check the actual devices API.\n\nActually, let me re-read the user's question: \"现在设备连接界面，为什么没有显示网关？网关信息和本机信息是哪里读取的\"\n\nThe user is asking:\n1. Why doesn't the device connection interface show the gateway?\n2. Where is the gateway info and local machine info read from? Note: local machine info, not PTZ device info.\n\nLet me look more carefully at the devices API to understand what data it returns and whether gateway is included.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_lxhs1koy8aj5q083nx8301lx","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"import requests; r=requests.get('http://127.0.0.1:10280/api/v1/devices', timeout=10); print('status:', r.st