{"type":"message","id":"c0bde5b5","parentId":"295b12e8","timestamp":"2026-06-30T16:53:25.172Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to understand what each of these calls does:\n\n1. Line 388 - Page load / initialization - This is where refreshDevices() is called on page load\n2. Line 614 - Tab switching - When user switches to devices tab\n3. Line 1148 - Inside discoverDevices() - After SADP discovery completes, refresh the device list\n4. Line 1163 - The function definition itself\n5. Lines 1288, 1416, 1448, 1509, 1532 - After various operations (add device, delete device, etc.) - These should stay\n6. Lines 2339, 2354 - After IP modification - These should stay\n\nThe key issues are:\n- Line 388: Page load calls refreshDevices() - This is problematic because refreshDevices() now calls POST /api/v1/devices/refresh which pings all devices. This is heavy on page load.\n- Line 614: Tab switch calls refreshDevices() - Same issue\n\nAccording to the boss's requirements:\n- Page load: Get device list (no status) → async refresh status\n- User clicks refresh: Call POST refresh API (ping)\n- No automatic refresh\n\nSo the fix is:\n1. Line 388: Change to call loadDevicesQuick() instead of refreshDevices()\n2. Line 614: Change to call loadDevicesQuick() instead of refreshDevices()\n\nLet me look at these lines more carefully and make the changes.\n\nLet me read line 388 context first.\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_fc7c0d09c2d84b87a55792d1","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":10,"offset":385,"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\web\\index.html"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":2981,"output":428,"cacheRead":135500,"cacheWrite":506,"totalTokens":139415,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782838386227,"responseId":"msg_3dc6fa9e-c405-4c18-bdc6-a35d6d5