重构。当前的问题是 POST /api/v1/devices/refresh 返回 405 错误。让我查找 refresh_devices 端点的定义。\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_26daf6bccf1a41d585b263d7","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":80,"offset":425,"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\api\\router.py"}},{"type":"text","text":"\n</think>\n\nThe user wants me to continue with the task. Let me review what I've been doing:\n\n1. I've been working on merging automatic and manual device logic in AstroHub\n2. I've modified router.py to simplify list_devices() and add refresh_devices() API\n3. I've modified sadp_discovery.py to make discovery instant (no waiting)\n4. I've modified devices.html to remove the \"source\" column\n5. I've modified index.html to update renderDevices() and refreshDevices() functions\n6. I've removed auto-refresh and auto SADP discovery\n\nNow I need to check if the refresh_devices endpoint is properly registered. Let me look at the router.py file to see if there's a route definition for POST /devices/refresh.\n\nLooking at my previous read, I can see the refresh_devices function is defined around line 440-490, but I need to check if it has the proper @api_router.post decorator.\n\nLet me continue the task by checking the route definition for refresh_devices and testing if the API works correctly. The POST /api/v1/devices/refresh is returning 405 Method Not Allowed, which means the route exists but the method is wrong. This suggests the route might not be defined as POST.\n\nLet me check the actual route definition.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_6ae982152ddd4402bf7431aa","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub && Select-String -Path src\\api\\router.py -Pattern \"def refresh_devices\" -Context 3,0"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":2601,"output":891,"cacheRead":143567,"cacheWrite":457,"totalTokens":147516,"cost":{"input":0,"output"