{"type":"message","id":"7184f463","parentId":"b114c391","timestamp":"2026-06-30T17:13:52.881Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the current code structure. Let me analyze what needs to change:\n\nCurrent `PTZDeviceController.__init__`:\n- Initializes config, clients, controllers, credentials, discovered cache\n- Does NOT initialize a persistent SADPManagerDLL instance\n\nCurrent `PTZDeviceController.discover_devices`:\n- Creates a NEW `SADPManagerDLL()` every call\n- Calls `mgr.discover_devices(timeout=3)` - waits 3 seconds\n- Returns devices or falls back to pure Python multicast\n\nThe boss's requirements:\n1. SADP runs in background continuously\n2. Click discover → instant return of already discovered devices\n3. No waiting\n\nWhat I need to do:\n1. In `__init__`: Create a persistent `SADPManagerDLL` instance and start SADP discovery\n2. In `discover_devices()`: Just return `self._sadp_mgr.discover_devices()` (which is already instant-return)\n3. Remove the timeout=3 logic\n4. Keep the SADPDevice dataclass conversion for backward compatibility\n\nLet me also check the `SADPManagerDLL` to understand its current instant-return behavior.\n\nActually, I already modified `SADPManagerDLL.discover_devices()` earlier to be instant-return:\n- If not started: start discovery + send inquiry\n- Return whatever devices are in `self._devices`\n\nThe key insight is: if SADP starts at `__init__` time, by the time user clicks \"discover\", there will already be devices cached. So `discover_devices()` just needs to call the persistent instance.\n\nLet me now make the edit to PTZDeviceController:\n\n1. Add `self._sadp_mgr = None` and SADP init in `__init__`\n2. Rewrite `discover_devices()` to use persistent instance\n\nLet me also check if `scan_for_devices` is used elsewhere and if I should keep the fallback.\n\nActually, the boss said \"精准修改，禁止过度开发\" (precise modification, no over-development). So I should:\n1. Keep the fallback logic minimal\n2. Focus on the core change: persistent SADP instance\n\nLet me also check what `SADPManagerDLL` is - it's imported from `src.core.sadp_discovery`. And `SADP_DLL_AVAILABLE` is a flag.\n\nNow let me write the edit. The key change is:\n1. In `__init__`, after loading credentials, start SADP:\n```python\n# 启动 SADP 后台发现\nself._sadp_mgr = None\nif SADP_DLL_AVAILABLE:\n    try:\n        self._sadp_mgr = SADPManagerDLL()\n        self._sadp_mgr.start_discovery()\n        self._sadp_mgr.send_inquiry()\n        LOG.log(\"done\", \"SADP 后台发现已启动\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        LOG.log(\"warning\", f\"SADP 启动失败: {e}\")\n```\n\n2. Rewrite `discover_devices()` to use persistent instance:\n```python\ndef discover_devices(self, bind_ip: str = \"0.0.0.0\") -> list[dict]:\n    \"\"\"返回已发现的设备列表（即时返回）。\"\"\"\n    if self._sadp_mgr:\n        # 发送 inquiry 刷新设备列表\n        self._sadp_mgr.send_inquiry()\n        sdk_devices = self._sadp_mgr.discover_devices()\n        if sdk_devices:\n            for dev_dict in sdk_devices:\n                dev = SADPDevice()\n                dev.mac = _normalize_mac(dev_dict.get(\"mac\", \"\"))\n                dev.ip = dev_dict.get(\"ip\", \"\")\n                dev.subnet_mask = dev_dict.get(\"subnet_mask\", \"\")\n                dev.gateway = dev_dict.get(\"gateway\", \"\")\n                dev.model = dev_dict.get(\"model\", \"\")\n                dev.serial_number = dev_dict.get(\"serial_number\", \"\")\n                dev.device_name = dev_dict.get(\"device_name\", \"\")\n                dev.firmware_version = dev_dict.get(\"firmware_version\", \"\")\n                dev.activated = dev_dict.get(\"activated\", False)\n                dev.is_hikvision = dev_dict.get(\"is_hikvision\", False)\n                self._discovered[dev.mac] = dev\n            return [self._sadp_to_dict(d) for d in self._discovered.values()]\n    \n    # Fallback: pure Python multicast\n    devices = scan_for_devices(bind_ip=bind_ip)\n    for d in devices:\n        d.mac = _normalize_mac(d.mac)\n        self._discovered[d.mac] = d\n    return [self._sadp_to_dict(d) for d in self._discovered.values()]\n```\n\nWait, I need to be more careful. The current code creates a new SADPManagerDLL each time and calls discover_devices(timeout=3). If I make it persistent, I need to ensure the SADP background thread keeps running.\n\nLooking at SADPManagerDLL.discover_devices() - I already modified it to be instant-return. But it also calls start_discovery() if not started. So if the SADP manager is created in __init__ and start_discovery() is called, the background thread should keep running.\n\nLet me check what start_discovery() does... Actually, I should just trust my earlier modification. The key change is:\n\n1. Create persistent SADPManagerDLL in __init__\n2. Start it (which starts the background callback thread)\n3. In discover_devices(), just call send_inquiry() and then get cached devices\n\nThis is the minimal change. Let me write it.\n\nActually, I need to be even more careful. Let me look at what `SADPManagerDLL.start_discovery()` does - it likely starts a background thread that listens for SADP callbacks. If it's already running, calling it again should be a no-op (there's likely a `_started` flag).\n\nLet me just make the edit and verify.\n现在修复核心问题。需要修改 `PTZDeviceController`：\n1. `__init__` 中启动持久化 SADP 后台实例\n2. `discover_devices()` 使用持久化实例，即时返回已发现设备\n3. 删除每次创建新实例 + timeout=3 的逻辑\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_f922fc9854a6436cb6df5b77","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"        self._credentials = {}\n        # 持久化 SADP 实例（后台持续运行，即时返回）\n        self._sadp_mgr = None\n        if SADP_DLL_AVAILABLE:\n            try:\n                self._sadp_mgr = SADPManagerDLL()\n                self._sadp_mgr.start_discovery()\n                self._sadp_mgr.send_inquiry()\n                LOG.log(\"done\", \"SADP 后台发现已启动\")\n            except Exception as e:\n                L