{"type":"message","id":"191a82ae","parentId":"cfe5e439","timestamp":"2026-06-30T17:14:39.902Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user says \"继续\" (continue). I was in the middle of fixing the PTZDeviceController. Let me review what I've done and what's left:\n\n1. **Already fixed**:\n   - SADP DLL path fix (added `SDK_LIBS_DIR / \"hik\" / \"Sadp.dll\"` search path)\n   - Device gateway display fix for SADP-only devices\n   - Speed test ZOOM grouping display\n   - Simplified `list_devices()` - removed source field, simplified logic\n   - Added `POST /devices/refresh` API with parallel ping\n   - Simplified SADP discovery to instant return\n   - Updated frontend: removed sourceBadge, removed auto-refresh, added loadDevicesQuick()\n   - Removed setInterval(refreshDevices, 15000) and autoSadpDiscover()\n   - Changed page init and tab switch to use loadDevicesQuick()\n\n2. **Just fixed**: PTZDeviceController to use persistent SADPManagerDLL instance instead of creating new one each time\n\nNow I need to:\n- Verify the fix works by testing\n- Check if there are any dead code to clean up\n- The `_sadp_to_dict` still has `\"source\": \"sadp\"` field - should I remove it? The boss said to remove the manual/auto distinction. Let me check.\n\nActually, looking at `_sadp_to_dict`, it still returns `\"source\": \"sadp\"`. But since we removed source from the device list API response, this might not matter. Let me check if `_sadp_to_dict` is used anywhere that still needs source.\n\nLooking at the flow:\n- `discover_devices()` returns dicts via `_sadp_to_dict()`\n- `get_discovered_devices()` returns dicts via `_sadp_to_dict()`\n- `list_devices()` in router.py uses `get_discovered_devices()` but then builds its own dict without source field\n- `refresh_devices()` in router.py also builds its own dict without source\n\nSo the `source` field in `_sadp_to_dict` is now dead data. I should remove it to be clean.\n\nBut wait - the boss said \"精准修改，禁止过度开发\" (precise modification, no over-development). The source field in `_sadp_to_dict` doesn't hurt anything, it's just unused data. Removing it could be considered over-development.\n\nActually, looking at the overall task, the boss's requirements are clear:\n1. ✅ MAC = unique identifier\n2. ✅ Remove manual/auto distinction\n3. ✅ SADP instant return\n4. ✅ Manual refresh only (no auto-ping)\n5. ✅ Device IP change shows new IP\n6. ✅ Online/offline/connected status via ping\n\nI think the main code changes are done. Let me verify by testing the API endpoints and check if there are any remaining issues.\n\nLet me test:\n1. Server health\n2. GET /api/v1/devices\n3. POST /api/v1/devices/refresh\n4. SADP discovery\n\nThen summarize what's been done.\n\nActually, the server is already running. Let me test the endpoints.\n\nWait - I need to check if the server needs to be restarted for the ptz_controller.py changes to take effect. The uvicorn --reload should auto-reload, but let me verify.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"好，`PTZDeviceController` 现在使用持久化 SADP 实例。现在验证修改是否生效——服务器有 `--reload` 应该自动加载：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_3f31b52a9e6249aeb39f496b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$env:NO_PROXY=\"*\"; Start-Sleep -Seconds 3; python -c \"import requests; r=requests.get('http://127.0.0.1:10280/api/v1/devices', timeout=10); print('GET /devices:', r.status_code); d=r.json(); print('  total:', d.get('total',0)); print('  data:', d.get('data',[]))\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_687443c2df2f419db87e92b2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$env:NO_PROXY=\"*\"; python -c \"import requests,time; t=time.time(); r=requests.post('http://127.0.0.1:10280/api/v1/devices/refresh', timeout=15); elapsed=round(time.time()-t,1); print('POST /refresh:', r.status_code, f'({elapsed}s)'); d=r.json(); print('  total:', d.get('total',0)); [print(f'  {x.get(\\\"ip\\\")}: {x.get(\\\"status\\\")}') for x in d.get('data',[])]\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu